key_points: Gabby Petito's death has been ruled as strangulation by Teton County Coroner Dr. Brent Blue.
Petito's case has attracted significant national attention, differentiating it from other missing person cases.
The exact date of Petito's death remains unclear, with the coroner estimating her body was left for 3-4 weeks before discovery.
The autopsy included a comprehensive examination but some details are withheld due to the ongoing investigation.
Petito's fiancé, Brian Laundrie, is still missing and has become a person of interest in the case.
Domestic violence has been highlighted as a significant aspect of the case, stemming from body camera footage of a dispute between Petito and Laundrie.
Concerning interactions and an 'odd text' have raised suspicions about the events leading to Petito's disappearance.
Laundrie, before disappearing, was under surveillance but wasn't detained, as detailed by North Port police.
He is not charged in Petito's death but was indicted for unauthorized use of financial accounts after her death.
The case continues to be a major point of discussion regarding missing persons and domestic violence in the US.
